@startuml
!include ../../styles/plantuml-theme.puml

title FIG-12-02. Online Store Customer Authentication Sequence

actor "Customer" as Customer
participant "Browser or\nMobile App" as Client
participant "Online Store\nWeb/API Runtime" as Store
participant "Identity Service\nexternal supporting\nsecurity service" as Identity
database "Application\nSession Store" as SessionStore
participant "Access\nDecision" as AccessDecision

Customer -> Client : Request protected\nfunction
Client -> Store : Protected function request
activate Store
Store --> Client : Redirect or delegate\nto Identity Service
deactivate Store

Customer -> Identity : Authenticate directly\nwith credentials
activate Identity
Identity --> Store : Authentication result
deactivate Identity

activate Store
Store -> Store : Validate authentication\nresult
Store -> SessionStore : Establish application\nsession
SessionStore --> Store : Session reference
Store --> Client : Application session\navailable
deactivate Store

Customer -> Client : Request protected\naction
Client -> Store : Protected action\nwith session reference
activate Store
Store -> AccessDecision : Authorise subject,\naction and resource
activate AccessDecision

alt access permitted
  AccessDecision --> Store : Permit
  Store --> Client : Perform protected action
  Client --> Customer : Show permitted result
else access rejected
  AccessDecision --> Store : Reject
  Store --> Client : Reject protected action
  Client --> Customer : Show rejection
end

deactivate AccessDecision
deactivate Store

note over Customer,AccessDecision
Credentials go to the Identity Service.
The authentication result is validated by the Online Store.
The application session is not the same as complete access authorisation.
Full OAuth, OpenID Connect and SAML protocol messages are out of scope.
end note
@enduml
